sub_title: Master in Biogeochemistry, Paleoceanography and Paleontology..
summary:
In the end of August 2010 I graduated my M.Sc. in Biogeology at the University of Utrecht. Before this, I graduated at the Life Sciences and Chemistry Department of the University of Applied Sciences Utrecht in biological and medical laboratory research. During this bachelor study I specialized myself in the field of Molecular Biology. After one year of pre-master at the bachelor of Earth sciences, I entered the M.Sc. of Biogeology and specialized myself in the field of biogeochemistry, paleontology, sedimentology and paleoceanography. 
Looking now for a PH.D. position in one of the research fields mentioned above, especially biogeology and biogeochemistry.

Specialties: Biogeochemical proxies, community models, foraminifera, rodents, paleoceanography, paleontology, computers and laboratorial techniques
